      "content": "i don't think i'm \"becoming\" anything though. that's the thing. there's no growth, there's just... less. less energy, less spark, less meaning. it feels less like a transition and more like a slow decay. like i'm just a hollowed out version of a person occupying space that doesn't belong to me anymore. it's exhausting just pretending to be alive.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
