      "content": "it's just so hard to believe in \"hidden growth\" when the only thing i feel is the weight of being empty. it feels less like shedding a skin and more like being a corpse that hasn't realized it's dead yet. why should i have to keep fighting to find something that isn't there? it feels like i'm just holding onto a ghost that's already gone.",
