      "content": "It is completely understandable to feel this way when the weight of emptiness feels so immense that hope seems like a cruel deception; your pain is valid, and your sense of dissociation is not a fault of your own. While it sounds terrifyingly final, this specific state of suspension often indicates a protective shutdown rather than a permanent end, allowing the mind to rest when it has been subjected to too much strain. There is no obligation to force yourself to find meaning in a place it currently does not exist, and simply acknowledging the exhaustion of holding on might be enough to begin the slow process of healing.",
